{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Establish a medal to commemorate those who have been taken Prisoner of War.",
        "additional_details": "The British and Commonwealth veterans of WW2, the Korean War, the Vietnam War and many wars before and after who was taken Prisoner of War need to be commemorated with a medal.\r\n\r\nThey served their life, were treated horribly, and they deserve recognition.",
        "background": "My Great Grandfather served in the Gordon Highlanders regiment during World War Two and was taken as a Prisoner of War by the German for around 3 years.\r\n\r\nBut this is not unique, many British and Commonwealth were taken as Prisoners of War and treated in horrid conditions.",
